reviewText: Not worth the money. You can find better interviews on youtube. The majority of these are poorly conducted interviews ripped from low budget radio stations and even one stolen from chelsea lately. Sadly there aren't even any live performances to accompany this fanmade compilation.
The interviews with Florence were very interesting and I enjoyed watching this DVD.
No snippets of concerts or anything, but lots of interviews.
Just interviews that I could watch for free on youtube.
Simply a bunch of spliced together interviews, and not very good ones at that.

Love Florence, and I was eagerly awaiting the release of How Big, How Beautiful - needless to say, I wasn't disappointed. This DVD complements that release well, in which Florence looks back over her career in a number of interviews. So happy the First Lady of contemporary music has returned!
Beautiful venue,beautiful voice,very relaxing. Would recommend.
